Studies on intercultural differences. Intercultural communication. Multiculturalism as a fact: national and religious subcultures in Estonia (minorities living in Estonia and religions operating here) Multiculturalism in education. Bennett's development model of cultural sensitivity and its adaptation to the educational context. Problems in intercultural communication. Taking cultural and religious background into account in teaching. Multicultural and intercultural teaching. Principles and skills of intercultural teaching.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is that students become aware of the religious and cultural diversity in Estonia and develop the ability to apply the principles of culturally sensitive teaching in their teaching.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student: - knows the peculiarities of the larger national and religious groups represented in Estonia, is able to find the necessary information about cultural groups; - takes into account the cultural heterogeneity in teaching in Estonia; - recognizes the misunderstandings that arise in a multicultural environment and offers solutions to them; - is able to create a learning environment that supports the involvement of the student's culture; - analyzes his / her intercultural teaching competence based on the development model of intercultural sensitivity
